Package org.variantsync.diffdetective.analysis

Class AnalysisResult

java.lang.Object
org.variantsync.diffdetective.analysis.AnalysisResult
All Implemented Interfaces:
Metadata<AnalysisResult>
public class AnalysisResult extends Object implements Metadata<AnalysisResult>
The result of a HistoryAnalysis. This result stores various metadata and statistics that we use for the validation of our ESEC/FSE paper. An AnalysisResult also allows to store any custom metadata or information.
Author:
Paul Bittner

    • AnalysisResult

      public AnalysisResult​(String repoName, int totalCommits, int exportedCommits, int emptyCommits, int failedCommits, int exportedTrees, double runtimeInSeconds, double runtimeWithMultithreadingInSeconds, CommitProcessTime min, CommitProcessTime max, DiffTreeSerializeDebugData debugData, ExplainedFilterSummary filterHits)
      Creates am analysis result with the given inital values.
      Parameters:
      repoName - The repo from which the results where collected.
      totalCommits - The total number of commits in the observed history of the given repository.
      exportedCommits - The number of commits that were processed. exportedCommits <= totalCommits
      emptyCommits - Number of commits that were not processed because they had no DiffTrees. A commit is empty iff at least of one of the following conditions is met for every of its patches: - the patch did not edit a C file, - the DiffTree became empty after transformations (this can happen if there are only whitespace changes), - or the patch had syntax errors in its annotations, so the DiffTree could not be parsed.
      failedCommits - Number of commits that could not be parsed at all because of exceptions when operating JGit. The number of commits that were filtered because they are a merge commit is thus given as totalCommits - exportedCommits - emptyCommits - failedCommits
      exportedTrees - Number of DiffTrees that were processed.
      runtimeInSeconds - The total runtime in seconds (irrespective of multithreading).
      runtimeWithMultithreadingInSeconds - The effective runtime in seconds that we have when using multithreading.
      min - The commit that was processed the fastest.
      max - The commit that was processed the slowest.
      debugData - Debug data for DiffTree serialization.
      filterHits - Explanations for filter hits, when filtering DiffTrees (e.g., because a diff was empty).

    • importFrom

      public static AnalysisResult importFrom​(Path p, Map<String,​BiConsumer<AnalysisResult,​String>> customParsers) throws IOException
      Imports a metadata file, which is an output of a AnalysisResult, and saves back to AnalysisResult.
      Parameters:
      p - Path to the metadata file
      customParsers - A list of parsers to handle custom values that were stored with putCustomInfo(String, String). Each parser parses the value (second argument) of a given key (first entry in the map) and stores it in the given AnalysisResult (first argument).
      Returns:
      The reconstructed AnalysisResult
      Throws:
      IOException - when the file could not be read.

    • storeAsCustomInfo

      public static Map.Entry<String,​BiConsumer<AnalysisResult,​String>> storeAsCustomInfo​(String key)
      Helper method to construct custom parsers for importFrom(Path, Map). This method creates a parser for custom values that just stores the parsed values as string values for the given key.
      Parameters:
      key - The key whose values should be stored as unparsed strings.
      Returns:
      A custom parser for importFrom(Path, Map).
